\int_0^\infty \frac{1}{x^2 + 2x + 2} \mathrm{d} x .
x^2+2x+2=(x+1)^2+1
 \int\limits_0^\infty \frac{dx}{x^2+2x+2}= \lim\limits_{t\to\infty}\int\limits_0^t\frac{dx}{x^2+2x+2}= \lim\limits_{t\to\infty} \arctan(x+1)|_0^t= 
 \lim\limits_{t\to\infty} \arctan(t+1)-\arctan(1)=\frac{\pi}{2}-\frac{\pi}{4}=\frac{\pi}{4} 
